This layer provides recipes for integrating BKK API components into Yocto.

Dependencies
============

Required layers:

  URI: /data/projects/yocto/poky/meta
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: /data/projects/yocto/meta-openembedded/meta-oe
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: /data/projects/bkk_display/meta-BKK-api
  branch: local


Adding the layer
================

Run:

  bitbake-layers add-layer /data/projects/bkk_display/meta-BKK-api


Provided recipe
===============

`bkk-api`:
- Fetches `git@github.com:danielpapa1166/bkk_api.git` from branch `main`
- Builds the C++ shared library from `cpp/`
- Installs `libbkk_api_shared.so` and public headers under `${includedir}/bkk_api`

`bkk-api-keyenv`:
- Installs the API key bootstrap service, helper script, and default key file under `/etc/bkk-api`
- Enables `bkk-api-keygen.service` to export the key into the runtime environment

`bkk-api-demo`:
- Builds the demo application binary and its application service
- Pulls in `bkk-api-keyenv` at runtime so the API key bootstrap service is present


Build example
=============

  bitbake bkk-api

